1. Setup:  
- Minimum:
  git config --global user.name "<your username>"
  git config --global user.email "<your email>"
- Verify:
  git config --list
- Another config may be saved in:
  /etc/gitconfig
  ~/.gitconfig
2. Start a git repository:
- Initialize (make) a local directory as git repository
  git init
- Clone (copy) repository from remote repository
  git clone 
3. Add new or modified file into staged mode
  git add <file>
  git add . # add all
4. Add file into commited state 
  git commit -m "<your message>"
5. Verify status
  git status
6. Clear all file in staged mode back to modified mode
  git restore --staged
  git restore <file>: restore a deleted file
7. restore current working directory to a previous commited staged 
  git checkout <commit_id>
8. Check log:
  git log
  git log --oneline
9. Different between current commited session and staged mode 
  git diff
  git diff <commit_id_1> <commit_id_2> # different between commited id
10. To ignore a file from git commit, add it into .gitignore
  .gitignore
11. Help
  git help 
  git <command> --help/-h 
  man git   